narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The course can seem intimidating at first, but I found myself enjoying it quite a bit. The texts are not really as bad as they seem. The class is considerable time commitment, so don't take it as a "fifth" or as a "gut" class, but don't feel that you need to be a French lit buff to take it - the course is accessible to pretty much anyone who has a minor interest in literature and who wants to improve particularly their written French.
